&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dryden HDU- Northwick Park Hospital Staff Nurse - (Band 5) Permanent; Full Time (37.5 hours/week) with the recent changes in Emergency care capacity at LNWUH we have a fabulous opportunity to recruit into our medical high dependency unit. We are seeking staffs with good clinical experience that are keen to advance their practice and team working skills. The applicant would be expected to work as a member team undertaking duties at Band 5 staff nurse level, with an emphasis on high standards of patient care, good clinical skills and the opportunity to enhance those skills. The post holder will be required to carry out clinical duties whilst maintaining good working relationships with colleagues and would be expected to work within the multidisciplinary team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dryden HDU is comprised of 24 beds which take patients from the Emergency Department and all medical wards. Our focus is on providing excellent care in a very busy environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The areas are complimented by a dedicated therapies and medical team and are supported by a clinical Matron and a shared clinical practice development nurse. There is a great opportunity for career progression and clinical and professional development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
